  "prompt": "Does Google take into account that you are speeding while calculating your ETA?",
  "response": "Google Maps does not specifically account for speeding or individual driving habits when calculating Estimated Time of Arrival (ETA). It generally uses average driving speeds, traffic conditions, road types, and historical data to provide ETA. Speeding may alter your actual arrival time compared to the ETA provided by Google Maps, but this is not directly factored into the initial calculation. It's important to adhere to speed limits for safety and legality, and the ETA should be treated as an approximate guide.",
